1
00:00:06,760 --> 00:00:11,197
<i>We are Fighting Dreamers aiming high</i>

2
00:00:11,265 --> 00:00:14,792
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>don't care what people think about them</i>

3
00:00:14,868 --> 00:00:18,304
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>follow what they believe</i>

4
00:00:18,372 --> 00:00:21,967
<i>Oli Oli Oli Oh! Just go my way</i>

5
00:00:22,042 --> 00:00:25,307
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

6
00:00:25,379 --> 00:00:27,313
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>

7
00:00:29,116 --> 00:00:32,051
<i>Down a difficult road</i>
<i>filled with endless struggles</i>

8
00:00:32,119 --> 00:00:35,919
<i>Where do you think you are going</i>
<i>following someone else's map?</i>

9
00:00:36,323 --> 00:00:43,161
<i>An insightful crow comes along</i>
<i>to tear up the map</i>

10
00:00:43,397 --> 00:00:50,462
<i>Now open your eyes and</i>
<i>take a look at the truth (Yeah!)</i>

11
00:00:50,771 --> 00:00:56,903
<i>There's nothing to lose,</i>
<i>so let's GO!!!</i>

12
00:00:57,044 --> 00:01:01,310
<i>We are Fighting Dreamers aiming high</i>

13
00:01:01,381 --> 00:01:04,976
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>don't care what people think about them</i>

14
00:01:05,052 --> 00:01:08,385
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>follow what they believe</i>

15
00:01:08,455 --> 00:01:12,084
<i>Oli Oli Oli Oh!</i>
<i>Just go my way</i>

16
00:01:12,159 --> 00:01:15,754
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

17
00:01:15,829 --> 00:01:19,321
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>
<i>We're gonna do it and do our best!</i>

18
00:01:19,399 --> 00:01:22,994
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

19
00:01:23,070 --> 00:01:27,166
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>
<i>We're gonna do it and do our best! BANG!</i>

20
00:01:30,321 --> 00:01:34,951
<i>The Third Hokage, Forever...</i>

21
00:01:47,972 --> 00:01:49,064
Sarutobi...

22
00:01:50,207 --> 00:01:52,368
At the very least this sword...

23
00:01:57,048 --> 00:01:59,278
<i>It was a fitting end for somebody like you</i>

24
00:01:59,350 --> 00:02:02,444
<i>who has mastered</i>
<i>the Way of the Shinobi.</i>

25
00:02:08,959 --> 00:02:12,190
It feels like my arms are burning...

26
00:02:12,496 --> 00:02:13,793
Master Orochimaru!

27
00:02:14,532 --> 00:02:16,124
This is where we call off our plan.

28
00:02:17,435 --> 00:02:20,063
Release the Barrier.
We'll head back.

29
00:02:20,538 --> 00:02:21,163
- Yes!
- Yes!

30
00:02:21,539 --> 00:02:22,403
- Release!
- Release!

31
00:02:26,610 --> 00:02:27,474
The Barrier...!

32
00:02:27,712 --> 00:02:28,474
It's released!

33
00:02:29,413 --> 00:02:30,573
Where is Lord Hokage?

34
00:02:36,787 --> 00:02:37,515
Let's go

35
00:02:39,557 --> 00:02:40,387
We won't let you get away!

36
00:02:44,528 --> 00:02:46,826
Ninja Art: Spider Web Net!

37
00:02:49,834 --> 00:02:52,302
An adhesive type of string
filled with Chakra...?

38
00:02:54,905 --> 00:02:57,567
Kakashi! They're on the move!
Do we go after them?

39
00:02:57,641 --> 00:02:59,074
No, wait, Guy.

40
00:02:59,610 --> 00:03:00,304
That's right...

41
00:03:01,212 --> 00:03:04,511
If you make a move without
any data on the situation up there,

42
00:03:04,915 --> 00:03:06,712
you will get caught in
the enemy's trap.

43
00:03:07,218 --> 00:03:09,209
I'm totally aware of that.

44
00:03:09,687 --> 00:03:11,211
But regardless of whether
there is a trap or not,

45
00:03:11,288 --> 00:03:13,688
we can't let the enemy get away
at a time like this!

46
00:03:13,958 --> 00:03:15,926
That is the way of the Leaf Shinobi!

47
00:03:16,694 --> 00:03:19,857
So... are you just going to watch?

48
00:03:20,531 --> 00:03:21,293
Kabuto?

49
00:03:25,302 --> 00:03:26,701
So you did know, after all.

50
00:03:27,104 --> 00:03:28,571
So... what are we going to do?

51
00:03:28,973 --> 00:03:30,372
It's about time that
we made a retreat.

52
00:03:31,108 --> 00:03:32,700
You're going to run away
from me again?

53
00:03:34,011 --> 00:03:35,273
Right now...

54
00:03:35,646 --> 00:03:39,548
if we show our cards,
they're most likely going to be copied.

55
00:03:40,751 --> 00:03:42,184
Then again,

56
00:03:42,253 --> 00:03:47,088
it doesn't seem like you've completely
mastered that eye like the Uchiha clan.

57
00:03:55,633 --> 00:03:56,361
Well then...

58
00:04:07,878 --> 00:04:08,742
Temari...

59
00:04:15,286 --> 00:04:16,253
Kankuro!

60
00:04:42,613 --> 00:04:43,841
I'm leaving Sakura with you.

61
00:04:46,116 --> 00:04:47,174
H-Hey!

62
00:05:01,999 --> 00:05:05,992
<i>Why is...this guy so strong?</i>

63
00:05:07,938 --> 00:05:09,929
<i>My existence will not disappear...</i>

64
00:05:11,041 --> 00:05:14,636
<i>I will not disappear!</i>
<i>I cannot disappear!</i>

65
00:05:36,901 --> 00:05:39,096
<i>I told you not to talk to that guy!</i>

66
00:05:39,536 --> 00:05:40,468
<i>Let's go.</i>

67
00:05:45,509 --> 00:05:48,069
<i>Oh, there! That's him...</i>

68
00:05:50,547 --> 00:05:51,514
<i>Go away!</i>

69
00:05:54,385 --> 00:06:00,381
<i>Monster! Monster! Monster...!</i>

70
00:06:09,867 --> 00:06:11,664
<i>You monster! Die!</i>

71
00:06:14,571 --> 00:06:17,540
<i>That's him... Don't get involved, fool!</i>

72
00:06:20,945 --> 00:06:22,344
<i>Don't look at him!</i>

73
00:06:25,449 --> 00:06:26,677
<i>Go away!</i>

74
00:06:50,841 --> 00:06:54,299
<i>To them, I'm just a relic of the past</i>
<i>who they want to see disappear.</i>

75
00:06:54,745 --> 00:06:59,409
<i>So what did I have in this life,</i>
<i>why did I keep living?</i>

76
00:07:02,319 --> 00:07:07,552
<i>And that time, I thought of myself that I...</i>
<i>no, that is what I had to think.</i>

77
00:07:08,726 --> 00:07:12,218
<i>And then knew that</i>
<i>it was the most painful thing.</i>

78
00:07:13,964 --> 00:07:19,561
<i>That I... that my existence didn't matter</i>
<i>to anyone else in the world.</i>

79
00:07:20,704 --> 00:07:22,695
D-Don't come any closer!

80
00:07:31,048 --> 00:07:37,317
The pain of... being all alone...
really is unbearable, isn't it?

81
00:07:40,758 --> 00:07:42,453
The way you feel...

82
00:07:42,993 --> 00:07:46,429
I don't know why,
but I completely understand that it hurts.

83
00:07:47,431 --> 00:07:52,459
But I've met people who are
very important to me now.

84
00:07:55,606 --> 00:08:00,441
I won't allow those important people...
to get hurt!

85
00:08:02,146 --> 00:08:08,574
If not, I will stop you even if
that means... that I have to kill you!

86
00:08:09,186 --> 00:08:10,153
Why...?

87
00:08:11,388 --> 00:08:14,551
How is it that you can fight so much
for other people?

88
00:08:15,426 --> 00:08:19,362
They saved me from the hell
of being all alone.

89
00:08:19,930 --> 00:08:22,228
They accepted me for who I was.

90
00:08:23,667 --> 00:08:26,932
That's why... they are important to me!

91
00:08:34,078 --> 00:08:38,777
<i>Love is a heart that desires to serve</i>
<i>a precious person who is close to oneself,</i>

92
00:08:38,849 --> 00:08:41,511
<i>to love and watch over that person...</i>

93
00:08:43,153 --> 00:08:44,620
<i>Love...</i>

94
00:08:46,423 --> 00:08:48,948
<i>That is why he is so strong?</i>

95
00:08:51,495 --> 00:08:52,928
That's enough, Naruto...

96
00:08:57,568 --> 00:08:58,967
Sakura is okay.

97
00:09:00,437 --> 00:09:02,371
This guy's Chakra must
have been depleted as well...

98
00:09:03,640 --> 00:09:05,574
Sakura's sand crumbled
a long time ago.

99
00:09:06,376 --> 00:09:08,207
Oh, I see...

100
00:09:15,252 --> 00:09:18,551
I've had enough... Stop here.

101
00:09:18,856 --> 00:09:19,754
Gaara?

102
00:09:25,129 --> 00:09:28,826
<i>I've never seen Gaara in such</i>
<i>a weakened state before...</i>

103
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:31,360
All right.

104
00:10:04,501 --> 00:10:06,901
<i>Naruto Uzumaki, huh?</i>

105
00:10:09,540 --> 00:10:12,100
LOVE
<i>One of these days, even I...</i>

106
00:10:15,679 --> 00:10:17,806
Temari... Kankuro...

107
00:10:18,215 --> 00:10:19,045
- Huh?
- Huh?

108
00:10:20,117 --> 00:10:21,049
Sorry...

109
00:10:25,756 --> 00:10:27,747
D-Don't worry about it...

110
00:12:23,674 --> 00:12:24,766
Rain...

111
00:12:25,809 --> 00:12:27,504
The sky has started to weep as well...

112
00:12:30,114 --> 00:12:31,741
We will begin the memorial service

113
00:12:31,815 --> 00:12:34,306
for the Third Hokage,
who lost his life in this battle,

114
00:12:34,385 --> 00:12:38,947
as well as the other victims
of this battle.

115
00:12:40,958 --> 00:12:42,152
It's started...

116
00:12:42,993 --> 00:12:46,451
In the end,
all we could do was just watch...

117
00:13:05,950 --> 00:13:07,247
<i>Why?</i>

118
00:13:08,986 --> 00:13:11,955
<i>Why did Old Man Hokage have to die?</i>

119
00:13:21,365 --> 00:13:22,332
<i>Why...?</i>

120
00:13:39,817 --> 00:13:41,808
It's already been a year...

121
00:13:43,487 --> 00:13:47,719
It's not easy to laugh
hiding your sadness.

122
00:13:48,459 --> 00:13:53,726
I heard from your teacher that
you're the center of laughter...

123
00:13:54,231 --> 00:13:56,324
I'm not sad at all!

124
00:13:56,700 --> 00:13:59,430
It's a very honorable thing for
a Shinobi to die doing their duty!

125
00:13:59,870 --> 00:14:01,667
My dad and mom sacrificed their lives

126
00:14:01,739 --> 00:14:04,833
to protect this village
from the Demon Fox...

127
00:14:04,908 --> 00:14:06,341
They're heroes!

128
00:14:06,677 --> 00:14:12,081
I am the child of the heroes!
I'm not sad to be alone.

129
00:14:13,650 --> 00:14:15,914
And besides, these are tears of joy.

130
00:14:15,986 --> 00:14:17,180
It's all right.

131
00:14:20,758 --> 00:14:25,195
I know that you're curled up
holding your knees by yourself.

132
00:14:26,864 --> 00:14:29,662
But you're not alone...

133
00:14:29,967 --> 00:14:30,490
Huh?

134
00:14:32,036 --> 00:14:36,871
The Ninja of the Hidden Leaf Village
have the will of fire...

135
00:14:37,508 --> 00:14:38,600
Will of fire...?

136
00:14:39,276 --> 00:14:42,609
It's the strong will to protect
the Leaf Village.

137
00:14:43,447 --> 00:14:50,080
As long as they have this will of fire,
everybody in this village are all family.

138
00:14:50,587 --> 00:14:54,614
Iruka... I wonder if you have it?

139
00:14:58,996 --> 00:14:59,894
Yeah...

140
00:15:22,653 --> 00:15:23,779
For Hayate?

141
00:15:29,226 --> 00:15:32,627
The Third Hokage's funeral
has already started. Make it quick.

142
00:15:33,964 --> 00:15:37,092
You too, Kakashi, is it for Obito...?

143
00:15:38,869 --> 00:15:41,565
If you're always thinking of
an excuse for your tardiness,

144
00:15:42,072 --> 00:15:44,131
you should just come earlier.

145
00:15:48,545 --> 00:15:50,740
I do... from early in the morning.

146
00:15:53,784 --> 00:15:55,877
It's just that,
whenever I come here

147
00:15:55,953 --> 00:16:00,049
I just want to punish myself
for being such a fool in the past.

148
00:16:06,530 --> 00:16:07,258
Humph...

149
00:16:34,124 --> 00:16:37,582
<i>Shinobi, no matter what kind</i>
<i>of situation they are in,</i>

150
00:16:37,661 --> 00:16:39,856
<i>cannot show their emotion.</i>

151
00:16:40,898 --> 00:16:42,832
<i>You must always prioritize your mission,</i>

152
00:16:43,167 --> 00:16:46,762
<i>and never shed a tear in</i>
<i>any kind of situation...</i>

153
00:17:46,863 --> 00:17:48,330
Iruka Sensei...

154
00:17:48,398 --> 00:17:49,023
Hmm?

155
00:17:50,300 --> 00:17:54,896
Why do people risk their own lives
for other people?

156
00:17:58,575 --> 00:18:01,738
When one person dies...

157
00:18:03,413 --> 00:18:07,645
their past, their present life, and their future
disappear along with them.

158
00:18:08,552 --> 00:18:11,783
Many people die doing their duty
and fighting in battle...

159
00:18:12,489 --> 00:18:15,947
And shockingly easily, too.

160
00:18:17,728 --> 00:18:19,662
Hayate was one of them.

161
00:18:20,797 --> 00:18:24,358
Those who pass away also
have dreams and ambitions.

162
00:18:25,502 --> 00:18:29,905
But everyone has something else,
just as important.

163
00:18:31,108 --> 00:18:37,638
Parents, siblings, friends, lovers...
Those who are dear to them.

164
00:18:39,016 --> 00:18:41,177
They trust each other and help each other,

165
00:18:41,752 --> 00:18:46,246
the people whom they've cherished
since the day they were born.

166
00:18:47,658 --> 00:18:50,218
And that string which connects
those people

167
00:18:50,294 --> 00:18:53,991
becomes stronger and
thicker as time goes by...

168
00:18:55,599 --> 00:18:57,191
It can't be explained by logic...

169
00:18:57,934 --> 00:19:03,634
Those who hold those strings just do it,
because it's important to them.

170
00:19:04,808 --> 00:19:08,676
Yeah, I kind of get it.

171
00:19:09,846 --> 00:19:10,676
But...

172
00:19:13,650 --> 00:19:15,174
It's tough to die.

173
00:19:16,586 --> 00:19:19,077
It's not like he just died for nothing.

174
00:19:20,157 --> 00:19:22,819
He left us something very important.

175
00:19:24,194 --> 00:19:27,288
Well, you'll eventually understand
one of these days.

176
00:19:27,831 --> 00:19:31,232
Yeah, I kind of get that too!

177
00:19:35,806 --> 00:19:37,637
The rain's stopped.

178
00:19:47,718 --> 00:19:49,709
Bye! Iruka Sensei!

179
00:19:49,953 --> 00:19:50,851
Yeah...

180
00:19:52,989 --> 00:19:57,085
<i>Lord Third Hokage,</i>
<i>the will of fire you spoke of</i>

181
00:19:57,494 --> 00:20:02,193
<i>seems to have been passed on</i>
<i>to the young Leaves.</i>

182
00:20:03,967 --> 00:20:07,459
<i>The flame in their hearts</i>
<i>which you lit</i>

183
00:20:07,738 --> 00:20:11,105
<i>will burn bright and strong...</i>

184
00:20:11,475 --> 00:20:15,605
<i>And it will shine upon this village,</i>
<i>and watch over and protect us.</i>

185
00:20:20,984 --> 00:20:25,648
<i>It will become a new Hokage...</i>
<i>one of these days...</i>

186
00:20:33,764 --> 00:20:36,494
They did manage to avoid annihilation,

187
00:20:36,767 --> 00:20:39,133
but it seems the damage
is pretty extensive.

188
00:20:39,603 --> 00:20:42,538
The village that was once
at the height of its glory...

189
00:20:43,206 --> 00:20:44,434
How sad...

190
00:20:47,210 --> 00:20:48,837
How unlike you.

191
00:20:49,346 --> 00:20:52,338
You have lingering affections
for your old home?

192
00:20:53,083 --> 00:20:54,380
Even you?

193
00:20:55,018 --> 00:20:57,578
No, not at all.

194
00:21:09,333 --> 00:21:13,269
<i>A cycle of hardship, right?</i>

195
00:21:14,271 --> 00:21:18,230
<i>Inside, we were crying, right?</i>

196
00:21:19,543 --> 00:21:27,643
<i>But the one thing we won't give up</i>
<i>is the dream we've chosen, right?</i>

197
00:21:28,485 --> 00:21:30,578
<i>It's a secondary role,</i>

198
00:21:33,357 --> 00:21:36,383
<i>a role in the shadows</i>

199
00:21:36,827 --> 00:21:41,764
<i>But in reaching for that dream,</i>

200
00:21:41,898 --> 00:21:47,632
<i>let us stay centered,</i>
<i>let us stay true</i>

201
00:21:47,904 --> 00:21:52,534
<i>Over and over,</i>
<i>we hung on without giving up</i>

202
00:21:52,609 --> 00:21:57,512
<i>Over and over,</i>
<i>we kept coming back up</i>

203
00:21:57,581 --> 00:22:06,751
<i>Over and over,</i>
<i>we believed and dreamed</i>

204
00:22:07,190 --> 00:22:12,321
<i>Over and over,</i>
<i>we've seen fools</i>

205
00:22:12,396 --> 00:22:17,993
<i>Over and over,</i>
<i>we've stood in the shadows of others</i>

206
00:22:19,636 --> 00:22:29,773
<i>Now, it's our turn...</i>
<i>Let us bask in our dreams</i>

207
00:22:35,852 --> 00:22:39,913
The ritual ends, and morning mist
will be covering all soon.

208
00:22:41,057 --> 00:22:42,217
Silence...

209
00:22:42,759 --> 00:22:46,820
In that white mist,
the shadow quietly sharpens its fangs.

210
00:22:48,131 --> 00:22:54,468
It awakens childhood memory,
disappointment, ire, and resolve.

211
00:22:56,139 --> 00:23:00,838
The cog wheel named destiny
slowly begins to turn...

212
00:23:02,279 --> 00:23:04,747
Next time: "Return of the Morning Mist"
